Class NoExecutorListAnalyzer

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Analyzer, Rule

    public class NoExecutorListAnalyzer
extends ListAnalyzer
    This list analyzer has no executor. In addition to that the list of the underlying analyzers can be fetched from the analyzer and thus these lists can be flattened when such an analyzer is a member of a list.

    This feature is used by the method GrammarDefinition.list(Analyzer...) when there are keyword lists in the argument. This type of list analyzer is returned by the method GrammarDefinition.kw(String...) when there are more than one arguments, and having that passed to the method list() the latter one is able to flatten it to a single list. This way 

     list( kw("A","B"), kw("C") )
    will have the same result as 
     list( kw("A"),kw("B"),kw("C") )
    Author:
    Peter Verhas
